<li class="commentbody" id="comment-341962">
			<cite><a href='http://www.jbsavor.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>jb SAVOR</a></cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-341962" title="">January 11, 2010</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">223</div>

				<p>A much belated post, but I thought I&#8217;d share for those that want to make this ahead of time.  I followed the recipe as Deb instructs through the first 30 minutes of baking.  I then flipped the pears over, baked an additional 15 minutes, and then let the pears come to room temperature.  When I was ready to finish the dish, I flipped the pears back over so the cut side was up and baked for an additional 15 minutes.  The sauce finished caramelizing perfectly, the pears were tender and delicious, and the house was filled with warm vanilla scents.  Perfect!</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
<li class="commentbody" id="comment-342911">
